00:13.896 --> 00:15.172
Les:
♪ I'm goin' down to South Park

00:15.275 --> 00:17.241
♪ Gonna have myself a time

00:17.344 --> 00:18.827
♪ Friendly faces everywhere

00:18.931 --> 00:20.689
♪ Humble folks
without temptation ♪

00:20.793 --> 00:23.758
Les:
♪ I'm goin' down to South Park,
gonna leave my woes behind ♪

00:23.862 --> 00:25.620
♪ Ample parking day or night

00:25.724 --> 00:27.379
♪ People spouting,
"Howdy, neighbor" ♪

00:27.482 --> 00:30.482
Les:
♪ Headin' on up to South Park,
gonna see if I can't unwind ♪

00:30.586 --> 00:32.068
♪ Murpph mmmph mmph
mmmph mrrr mff mrmmph! ♪

00:32.172 --> 00:33.862
♪ Murpph mmmph mmph mmmph
mrrr mff mrmmph! ♪

00:33.965 --> 00:37.103
Les:
♪ Come on down to South Park,
and meet some friends of mine ♪

00:40.310 --> 00:42.793
Come on, guys.
We don't wanna be late.

00:42.896 --> 00:45.172
Do I have to go? It's the only
day I get to play games.

00:45.275 --> 00:48.379
We're all going.
Come on.

00:49.862 --> 00:51.862
I don't understand why we have
to go to church every Sunday.

00:51.965 --> 00:53.724
Church is important,
Stan.

00:53.827 --> 00:56.172
Way more important
than video games and TV.

00:56.275 --> 00:58.517
Church is about community
and coming together --

00:58.620 --> 00:59.896
a lot of things.

01:00.000 --> 01:02.862
All I know is that after church,
I just feel better.

01:02.965 --> 01:05.000
Yeah.
Me, too.

01:05.103 --> 01:07.034
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:07.137 --> 01:08.482
Hey, mornin', Stephen,
Linda!

01:08.586 --> 01:10.000
Morning, guys.

01:10.103 --> 01:11.689
Man:
Oh, thanks, there, Randy.

01:11.793 --> 01:13.068
You got it.
Where's Josie?

01:13.172 --> 01:14.793
Aw, she slipped her disc
in her neck.

01:14.896 --> 01:16.172
Poor thing
can barely move.

01:16.275 --> 01:17.655
Aw, she's gonna miss church?
That's too bad.

01:17.758 --> 01:19.000
Give her my best.

01:19.103 --> 01:20.689
[ Conversations stop ]

01:20.793 --> 01:22.482
For God so loved the world

01:22.586 --> 01:24.827
that he gave
his only begotten son

01:24.931 --> 01:27.965
so that whoever believed in him
should have eternal life.

01:28.068 --> 01:29.793
This is the gospel of the Lord.

01:29.896 --> 01:32.448
Townspeople: Praise to you,
Lord Jesus Christ.

01:32.551 --> 01:35.586
Today's gospel talks about
what the Lord has to give us.

01:35.689 --> 01:39.310
He did so because we could not
control our temptations.

01:39.413 --> 01:41.551
Kind of like a priest
in a room full of naked boys.

01:41.655 --> 01:44.689
[ Townspeople snicker ]

01:44.793 --> 01:46.000
Okay. Okay.

01:46.103 --> 01:47.896
Let's -- let's try and have
none of that today.

01:48.000 --> 01:51.655
In John 3:16, the gospel tells
us how God so loved the world,

01:51.758 --> 01:53.689
he gave to us his only son.

01:53.793 --> 01:55.689
And a Catholic priest
raped him.

01:55.793 --> 01:57.586
[ Laughter ]

01:57.689 --> 02:00.068
Okay, okay.
Come -- Come on, guys.

02:00.172 --> 02:02.862
N-Now, what greater gift
could the Lord have given to us?

02:02.965 --> 02:04.000
Children's underwear

02:04.103 --> 02:05.724
which priests couldn't
pull down so easily.

02:05.827 --> 02:07.275
[ Laughter ]

02:07.379 --> 02:09.862
Okay. Let's -- Let's try
and compose ourselves.

02:09.965 --> 02:13.034
Let's try and just get through
this first one, okay, guys?

02:13.137 --> 02:16.000
What does it mean that the Lord
gave us his only begotten son?

02:16.103 --> 02:17.172
It means
if you're a cute boy

02:17.275 --> 02:18.551
at a Catholic priest
swimming party,

02:18.655 --> 02:19.620
you better be gettin'!

02:19.724 --> 02:23.034
[ Laughter ]

02:26.172 --> 02:27.482
[ Laughter continues ]

02:27.586 --> 02:29.034
Oh, that was a great one,
Nelson.

02:29.137 --> 02:30.724
Salvation
in a little boy's mouth.

02:30.827 --> 02:32.172
I'm gonna post that one
for sure.

02:32.275 --> 02:34.103
Who said the thing
about naked boy salad?

02:34.206 --> 02:35.275
Oh, that was Linda!

02:35.379 --> 02:37.172
Well, see ya next week,
everybody!

02:37.275 --> 02:39.172
-Yeah! See ya!
-All right. Take it easy, now!

02:39.275 --> 02:40.379
-Bye.
-That was good.

02:40.482 --> 02:43.379
I really don't understand
the point of all that.

02:43.482 --> 02:45.482
Yeah, well, I used
to think that about church

02:45.586 --> 02:46.862
when I was a kid,
too.

02:46.965 --> 02:49.000
But back then, I don't know
if church was that stupid.

02:49.103 --> 02:50.793
Hey, don't say
things like that, Stan.

02:50.896 --> 02:52.517
You wanna go
to fuckin' hell?

02:59.827 --> 03:01.896
[ Door creaks ]

03:07.344 --> 03:09.379
[ Sighs ]

03:13.206 --> 03:14.862
Father,
can I talk to you?

03:14.965 --> 03:18.379
Of course, my child.
What's troubling you?

03:18.482 --> 03:22.413
Well,
what's troubling you?

03:24.241 --> 03:26.310
You know, at school,
the kids used

03:26.413 --> 03:28.379
to all make fun
of me sometimes.

03:28.482 --> 03:30.241
One kid would say
something mean,

03:30.344 --> 03:31.827
and then the other kids
would laugh.

03:31.931 --> 03:34.413
I know how lousy
it feels.

03:34.517 --> 03:36.758
I learned
to just walk away,

03:36.862 --> 03:38.517
not give 'em
all the satisfaction.

03:38.620 --> 03:41.482
Well, we can't all
walk away.

03:41.586 --> 03:44.068
The -- The priesthood
is all I know.

03:44.172 --> 03:47.137
I-I dedicated
my entire life to it.

03:47.241 --> 03:49.551
I don't know
anything else.

03:49.655 --> 03:51.586
I know it seems
impossible.

03:51.689 --> 03:53.413
I thought I'd be a punching bag
my whole life,

03:53.517 --> 03:56.241
but now, I'm one
of the popular kids.

03:56.344 --> 03:57.310
I even get invited

03:57.413 --> 03:59.310
to board game night
at Stan's house.

03:59.413 --> 04:01.620
My point is,
sometimes,

04:01.724 --> 04:04.137
y-you just gotta
put yourself out there.

04:10.344 --> 04:12.103
I wanna be Calamity Jane
this time.

04:12.206 --> 04:13.586
How many cards
do you start with, Kenny?

04:13.689 --> 04:15.172
Two cards.[ Door opens ]

04:15.275 --> 04:16.551
Oh.
There's Butters!

04:16.655 --> 04:17.896
Oh, hey, fellas!

04:18.000 --> 04:19.517
I hope you don't mind
I brought a friend.

04:19.620 --> 04:21.137
Come on in!

04:21.241 --> 04:23.103
Uh, hello, my children.

04:24.862 --> 04:27.689
Okay, so, I-I guess
I'm gonna go to the saloon

04:27.793 --> 04:29.137
and try
to arrest Cartman.

04:29.241 --> 04:30.482
Let's see what you got,
bitch.

04:30.586 --> 04:34.482
So, Kyle, did you know
Father is a really good singer?

04:34.586 --> 04:35.965
You like to sing, too,
don't you?

04:36.068 --> 04:37.344
No.

04:37.448 --> 04:39.310
Praise the Lord
for the Lord is good.

04:39.413 --> 04:42.206
Sing praise to his name,
for that is pleasant.

04:42.310 --> 04:43.206
Ace.
You lose.

04:43.310 --> 04:44.586
Randy: Hey, Stan.

04:44.689 --> 04:46.793
Have you seen my --

04:50.724 --> 04:52.000
No way!

04:52.103 --> 04:54.586
Hang on! Hang on!
I gotta post this!

04:54.689 --> 04:56.000
I shouldn't be here.

04:56.103 --> 04:57.206
This is hilarious.

04:57.310 --> 04:58.896
Four boys and a priest
playing a board game!

04:59.000 --> 05:00.758
Aw, Father wait a --I should go.

05:00.862 --> 05:02.758
No, no, no wait.
Let me get the picture.

05:02.862 --> 05:04.448
Father!

05:04.551 --> 05:06.172
Aw, shit!
I missed it.

05:06.275 --> 05:07.344
Ugh.

05:07.448 --> 05:09.137
Why did you invite Butters
to game night?

05:09.241 --> 05:11.448
I didn't invite him.

05:11.551 --> 05:13.862
Come on, Father.
You can't give up so fast!

05:13.965 --> 05:15.931
This is just gonna
make things way worse.

05:16.034 --> 05:17.241
People will rip on me.

05:17.344 --> 05:19.413
Who cares?
Who cares what people say?

05:19.517 --> 05:20.448
I do.

05:20.551 --> 05:21.862
Aw, come on.
You gotta be strong!

05:21.965 --> 05:23.862
Why do you care?!

05:23.965 --> 05:26.586
Because I was you.
Okay?

05:26.689 --> 05:29.689
I wasn't always this cool.
I've been through it.

05:29.793 --> 05:32.000
But then, one day,
somebody told me something.

05:32.103 --> 05:34.620
He said, "Life is full of love
and light and bountiful things,"

05:34.724 --> 05:35.862
and you know
who told me that?

05:35.965 --> 05:38.758
You did!
Two years ago in church!

05:38.862 --> 05:40.827
You have a right
to go and be happy,

05:40.931 --> 05:42.758
and if people wanna
keep trying to knock you down,

05:42.862 --> 05:44.931
well, fuck 'em!

05:47.206 --> 05:48.965
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:49.068 --> 05:50.413
Hey.
Morning, Mackey.

05:50.517 --> 05:52.931
Happy Sunday!
Mornin', Ted, Hazel.

05:53.034 --> 05:54.862
Townspeople:
Mornin'! Mornin'!

05:54.965 --> 05:56.172
Mornin'! Mornin'!

05:56.275 --> 05:57.827
Ah, doin' better.
huh, Josie?

05:57.931 --> 05:59.448
A lot better,
thank you.

05:59.551 --> 06:00.724
All right.

06:00.827 --> 06:02.068
[ Door handle rattles ]

06:02.172 --> 06:04.103
[ Grunts ]

06:04.206 --> 06:05.758
Huh.

06:05.862 --> 06:07.413
What the...?

06:07.517 --> 06:08.620
It's not open.

06:08.724 --> 06:09.827
Let me try.

06:09.931 --> 06:11.034
[ Door handle rattles ]

06:11.137 --> 06:13.931
Hey!
Hey, it's 9:00! Hey!

06:14.034 --> 06:15.379
What's going on?

06:15.482 --> 06:17.793
[ Lock disengages, door opens ]

06:19.241 --> 06:20.517
Ohhhhh!

06:20.620 --> 06:22.241
[ Laughter ]

06:22.344 --> 06:23.758
There's no church
today!

06:23.862 --> 06:25.931
You all are just gonna have
to find something better to do!

06:26.034 --> 06:28.000
[ Door slams, lock clicks ]

06:28.103 --> 06:29.344
Hey.

06:29.448 --> 06:30.758
Hey!
Open the door!

06:30.862 --> 06:33.620
Hey!
Come on! [ Grunts ]

06:35.724 --> 06:36.827
Well, this sucks.

06:36.931 --> 06:38.862
What are we supposed to do
without church?

06:38.965 --> 06:41.172
I just feel
so empty.

06:41.275 --> 06:42.724
What are you guys
so upset about?

06:42.827 --> 06:44.379
Shut up, Shelly!

06:46.034 --> 06:47.896
Isn't this great,
Father?

06:48.000 --> 06:49.344
Fresh, mountain air.

06:49.448 --> 06:50.758
Nice, warm fire.

06:50.862 --> 06:54.034
I have to admit, it's a pretty
nice way to spend a Sunday.

06:54.137 --> 06:56.241
How many are your works,
Lord?

06:56.344 --> 06:58.482
In wisdom,
you made them all.

06:58.586 --> 07:01.172
[ Giggles ] Yeah.
The Lord's pretty cool.

07:01.275 --> 07:02.517
He is...

07:02.620 --> 07:04.931
because
he brought me you.

